##157 confirmed cases, 11 towns "closed" ! Italy is the worst affected country in Europe...

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

As of midnight local time on the 24th, a total of 157 cases of new coronavirus pneumonia were confirmed in Italy, 2 were cured and discharged, 1 new death case and 3 cumulative deaths. The victim was an elderly woman suffering from cancer who died after being diagnosed with the new coronavirus, the Associated Press News Agency reported.

So far, health authorities have failed to locate patient zero, who caused the spread of the virus, said Italian Emergency Civil Defense Minister David Borrelli Borrelli. Some places have previously screened Chinese nationals or Italian citizens with a history of Chinese travel for the virus.

In terms of confirmed cases, Italy has become the most affected country in Europe and the most affected country in the world outside Asia.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The government has declared 11 northern towns closed

To curb the spread of the epidemic, Italian Prime Minister Contes 22 night announced a series of emergency measures, blockading Lombardy, Veneto and other cities and towns. About 50,000 people are restricted, police will tighten control, if necessary, the military.

The government of Italy stated that people who violated the quarantine of the affected areas would be considered a crime and would be subject to criminal penalties up to three months'imprisonment.

The prime minister, Contes, said such strict controls could be applied to other areas, depending on the development of the epidemic. He implied that a "suspension of visa issuance by Italy for Schengen" could not be ruled out.

The two regions are the rich and industrial heart of Italy, accounting for 30% of GDP. The Lombardy region, which includes the financial hub of Milan, has called for the closure of all schools, museums and libraries and the cancellation of cultural, religious and sports events. Three Serie A football matches on the 23rd were also cancelled.

Veneto's regional chief executive, Luca Zaia, has called a halt to the carnival, which runs from February 8 to 25, after a diagnosis was also made in the resort city of Venice. From 1 March, all public and private gatherings in the area will be banned, and schools, universities and museums will be closed.

Austria suspends passenger trains with Italy

Austrian Federal Railway Company (OBB) has suspended passenger train services with Italy via the Brenner Pass to stop further transmission of Covid-19, the China Standard Time said Sunday.

"The Brenner Pass and Italian passenger trains have been stopped in both directions, " a company spokesman said

This crossing over the Alps is an important and often congested passenger train route between Italy, Austria and Germany.

Shortly before the suspension was announced, the Austrian government said it had refused entry to a train from Venice, Italy, to Munich, Germany, on suspicion that two passengers on board might have been infected with COVID-19.

Austrian Interior Minister Karl Nehammer said earlier Sunday that a working group dealing with the outbreak would meet on Monday to discuss whether to impose border controls with Italy. This kind of border control can be set up in an hour.

There are now 181 suspected cases of COVID-19 in Austria, but no confirmed cases, the interior minister said.

The Chinese Embassy in Italy issued a warning

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
China Standard Time, the Chinese Embassy in Italy issued a warm reminder to strengthen self protection against the development of the new crown pneumonia epidemic in Italy, saying that recently, the new crown pneumonia epidemic has changed a lot in Italy, on February 21, the Italian Ministry of Health issued an emergency health regulation requiring all personnel who have visited relevant areas of China within 14 days to report to the local Health Bureau (ASL) , quarantined observation and supervision at the residence as directed by the staff of the Department of Health. Lombardy 见 Lombardia，Reg. has suspended business activities other than public needs and in-house production, encouraged telecommuting, and suspended recreational and educational activities for children.

Since the outbreak of the new crown disease, the majority of overseas Chinese have consciously carried out more stringent voluntary isolation measures, in the epidemic prevention and control has achieved good results. Inviting the vast number of overseas Chinese to further enhance their awareness of epidemic prevention, control and self-protection, and to abide by the health regulations promulgated by the Ministry of Health of Italy and the relevant regional governments on the basis of existing voluntary and conscious measures, remind and help the person who returned from home to the local Health Bureau (ASL) to record in time within 14 days, and take the necessary protective measures.

If the overseas Chinese have suspected symptoms, please call the 1500 hotline of the Ministry of Health for Guidance and assistance.
